title: Mini-quake in yakima county
author: Seattle Times Staffseattle Times News Services
text: SEATTLE - A small earthquake rattled a remote area in Southern Yakima County this morning. The University of Washington geophysics center reported that the magnitude 3.1 temblor struck at 8:45 a.m. and was centered 34 miles south of Yakima and at a depth of 11 miles. No damage was reported.
